Feel free to do any or all of the following - any help is most welcome. When contributing, always consider your own protection and safety as the first priority, particularly if you are at risk.

=== Spread Awareness ===
Tell your friends, family and acquaintances about Whonix. Post [https://www.whonix.org/blog/ Whonix news] on your website, blog or social media.

=== Follow Whonix ===
Follow one or more of the following sources: <ref>First consider the risk of following Whonix on social media in your personal circumstances.</ref>

* [[Stay_Tuned#Whonix_News_Blogs|Whonix News Blogs]]
* [https://twitter.com/Whonix Whonix Twitter Profile]
* [https://www.facebook.com/Whonix Whonix Facebook Profile]
* [https://plus.google.com/108150429836421683225/ Whonix Google+ Profile]

=== Provide Feedback ===
Send [https://forums.whonix.org feedback] about Whonix to the user forums.

=== Wikipedia Editing ===
Please help to improve [https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Whonix Whonix's Wikipedia Page]. <ref>Be aware that Tor exit nodes are usually prevented from editing.</ref> See the [https://forums.whonix.org/t/wikipedia-page-corrections/484 feedback thread] for further information.

=== Testing ===
Whonix needs more people to test new Whonix features, bug fixes and so on.

* Join us in testing new [[AppArmor]] profiles for improved security! Visit the [https://forums.whonix.org/c/apparmor Whonix AppArmor Forum].
* Perform [[Test|numerous activity tests]] on both Whonix-Workstation and Whonix-Gateway, while running a separate, testers-only Whonix version based on the [[Whonix-APT-Repository#Whonix_APT_Repository_Overview|stable-proposed-updates APT repository]].
* Test major, new Whonix versions prior to stable release - latest testers-wanted posts can be found here: https://www.whonix.org/blog/category/testers-wanted/

{{Anchor|Backup Whonix}}
=== Run the Whonix Backup Script ===

Create a backup of the Whonix Anonymous Operating System website and source code. The more people that retain backups, the less likely Whonix can be erased from the history books. This can be done periodically, every now and then or when convenient.

See: [[WhonixBackupScript| How to Backup Whonix]] for further details.

=== Screenshots ===

Whonix requires more recent and awesome [[Screenshots]]. Donate them to Whonix or release them into the [https://creativecommons.org/publicdomain/zero/1.0/ public domain].

=== Videos ===

We need more Whonix [[Videos]], particularly in languages other than English. They can be demonstration videos, promotional videos, conceptual videos or tutorials. Donate them to Whonix or release them into the [https://creativecommons.org/publicdomain/zero/1.0/ public domain]. We also have a video script waiting to be produced - please get in contact for further details.

=== Social Media / Marketing ===
Although social media platforms erode privacy goals by collecting a lot of user data, we believe they are important venues for marketing and communication in the modern era.

If you are willing to help or to maintain Whonix's Twitter, Google+, YouTube or identic.ca accounts or Facebook page, please get in [[Contact|contact]].


